questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;an angry look&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Scowl&lt;/strong&gt; means&amp;nbsp;to look at someone or something with a very angry&amp;nbsp;expression&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;(किसी व्यक्ति या वस्तु को बहुत गुस्से में अभिव्यक्ति के साथ देखना)&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Example -&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;The boss manifested his disgust with a &lt;strong&gt;scowl.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, it can be concluded that the meaning of the word &amp;#39;scowl&amp;#39; is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;an angry look&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;​&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;​&lt;/strong&gt;Hence, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option (3).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Anxious&lt;/strong&gt; means&amp;nbsp;feeling or showing worry, or nervousness&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;(चिंता, घबराहट दिखाना)&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Example -&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;She was extremely &lt;strong&gt;anxious &lt;/strong&gt;about her exams.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

The correct answer is-&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;Continuance&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;let&amp;#39;s look at the meaning of the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;given word&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;correct answer.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cessations&lt;/strong&gt;(noun):&amp;nbsp;Ending or stopping. (समाप्त या रुकना।)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(48, 51, 54); font-variant-ligatures: no-common-ligatures; letter-spacing: 0.2px;&quot;&gt;​&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&lt;i&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Religious leaders have called for a total cessation of the bombing campaign.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Continuance&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);&quot;&gt;(noun):&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;Something that is connected to something else, or the state of being continued. (ऐसा कुछ जो किसी और चीज से जुड़ा हो, या जारी रहने की अवस्था।)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;It&amp;rsquo;s really just a &lt;strong&gt;continuation &lt;/strong&gt;of the same street but called by a different name.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
		&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, the word&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Continuance&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the most appropriate antonym for&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Cessations&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s explore the meaning of other options&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shutoff&lt;/strong&gt;(verb):&amp;nbsp;To prevent something from being reached or seen. (किसी चीज को पहुंचने या देखने से रोकना।)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;The music room is &lt;strong&gt;shut off &lt;/strong&gt;from the rest of the house by a soundproof wall.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Halt&lt;/strong&gt;(verb):&amp;nbsp;To stop moving or doing something or happening. (हिलना या कुछ करना या बंद करना।)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;Production has &lt;strong&gt;halted &lt;/strong&gt;at all of the company&amp;#39;s factories because of the pay dispute.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stop&lt;/strong&gt;(verb): To finish doing something that you were doing. (आप जो कुछ कर रहे थे उसे पूरा करना।)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;Once I start eating chocolate, I can&amp;#39;t &lt;strong&gt;stop&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;Amnesia.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41); display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Amnesia&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; refers to a condition characterized by the partial or complete loss of memory. (याद्&amp;zwnj;दाश्&amp;zwj;त खो बैठने की अवस्&amp;zwj;था; स्&amp;zwj;मृति-लोप)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This loss of memory can be temporary or permanent and may affect various aspects of a person&amp;#39;s life, including their personal experiences, identity, and knowledge.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;So, a partial or total loss of memory is called &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Amnesia.&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The correct answer is &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Option 2&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Ascetic: &lt;/b&gt;not allowing yourself physical pleasures, especially for religious reasons. (विशेषतः धार्मिक कारणों से भौतिक सुखों से विमुख)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Atheist: &lt;/b&gt;a person who disbelieves or lacks belief in the existence of God or gods. (नास्तिक, निरीश्&amp;zwj;वरवादी)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Axiom: &lt;/b&gt;a rule or principle that most people believe to be true. (सब से स्&amp;zwj;वीकृत सिद्घांत या नियम; स्&amp;zwj;वयं-सिद्घ कथन)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The incorrect spelling among the given options is consceince. Its correct spelling is:&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;conscience&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Let us find out the meanings of the given&amp;nbsp;words:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Brethren&lt;/strong&gt; means the archaic plural of brother.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Conscience&lt;/strong&gt; means a person&amp;rsquo;s moral sense of right and wrong., viewed as acting as a guide to one&amp;rsquo;s behavior.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cabinet&lt;/strong&gt; means a cupboard with drawers or shelves for storing or displaying articles.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fondle&lt;/strong&gt; means to stroke or caress lovingly or erotically.&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
Thus, &lt;strong&gt;option 2&lt;/strong&gt; is the correct answer.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;

questions.statement:
Select the most appropriate option to fill in the blank.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The concert was _______ due to the bad weather.

questions.explanation:
&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;cancelled&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The word &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;cancelled&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; means to decide that an event will not take place. (रद्द किया गया)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The concert was called off due to the bad weather, which is appropriately expressed by the word &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;cancelled&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The other options: &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;celebrated&lt;/strong&gt;,&amp;quot; &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;continued&lt;/strong&gt;,&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;commenced&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; do not fit the context as appropriately.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;​Therefore, the correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 3&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Complete Sentence:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;The concert was &lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;cancelled&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt; due to the bad weather.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Celebrated (मनाया गया)&lt;/strong&gt;: means to honor or mark an occasion.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Continued (जारी रखा)&lt;/strong&gt;: means to carry on or persist.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Commenced (शुरू किया गया)&lt;/strong&gt;: means to begin or start.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;C&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;There is an error in &lt;strong&gt;part (c)&lt;/strong&gt;. The correct phrase is &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;mechanical energy by a heat engine&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The correct &lt;strong&gt;preposition&lt;/strong&gt; should be &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;by&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; as it refers to &lt;strong&gt;the agent or source of the action&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Off&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; is incorrect and should be replaced with &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;by&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In this &lt;strong&gt;sentence&lt;/strong&gt;, the heat is being absorbed and converted into mechanical energy &lt;strong&gt;by&lt;/strong&gt; the heat engine, not &lt;strong&gt;off of&lt;/strong&gt; it.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;​Thus, &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;option 1&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt; is the correct answer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Correct sentence&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;The heat absorbed is converted into&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;mechanical energy by&amp;nbsp;a heat engine.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;lsquo;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Part B&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;rsquo;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br style=&quot;&quot; /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot; display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;The above sentence is grammatically incorrect.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The error lies in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;part B&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the given sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given above sentence is an example of a&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;superlative&amp;nbsp;degree of adjective&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;As per the general rule,&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;never use &amp;lsquo;more or most&amp;rsquo; with adjectives that give absolute sense&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;These adjectives are:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;quot;unique, perfect, matchless, excellent, ideal, absolute, universal, impossible, whole, full, complete, eternal&amp;quot;,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;This church is a &lt;strong&gt;perfect &lt;/strong&gt;example of medieval architecture. (correct)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;This church is a &lt;strong&gt;most perfect&lt;/strong&gt; example of medieval architecture. (incorrect)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;​&lt;/em&gt;According to the explanation and example that are given above, &amp;lsquo;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;unique&lt;/span&gt;&amp;rsquo; is the correct use in place of &amp;ldquo;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;most unique&lt;/span&gt;&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Correct sentence:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;Each person&amp;#39;s genetic code is unique except in the case of identical twins.&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;As per the general rule, &lt;strong&gt;do not use double comparative adjectives or superlative adjectives.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;rsquo;s have a look at the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;structural form&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the given rule:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject +&amp;nbsp;verb + superlative degree + in/of +&amp;nbsp;object.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;Example:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;He is the &lt;strong&gt;silliest &lt;/strong&gt;person I know.&amp;nbsp;(correct)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;He is the &lt;strong&gt;most silliest&lt;/strong&gt; person I know.&amp;nbsp; (incorrect)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;glad to&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Glad&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; is an adjective that means &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;feeling or showing pleasure or satisfaction&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;To&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; is a preposition that indicates the direction or purpose of an action.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;See&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; is a verb that means &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;to perceive with the eyes&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;glad to see&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; is a collocation that means &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;to be pleased or satisfied to see someone&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;​Therefore, the correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 1&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Complete Sentence&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;I am &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;glad to&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; see you again.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Happy in&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; is incorrect because &amp;quot;in&amp;quot; is not used to indicate the direction or purpose of an action.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Happy at&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; is incorrect because &amp;quot;at&amp;quot; is not used to indicate the direction or purpose of an action.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Generous to&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; is incorrect because &amp;quot;generous&amp;quot; is not related to the verb &amp;quot;see.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;As soon as&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Conjunction-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;It is a word used for joining other sentences or phrases.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;And&amp;#39;, &amp;#39;but&amp;#39;, &amp;#39;or&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;are conjunctions.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;As soon as&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; -&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;immediately at or shortly after the time that.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;They say that &lt;strong&gt;as soon as&lt;/strong&gt; they walked in the door, something began happening within them.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;the appropriate conjunction for the given sentence is &amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;As soon as&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;​Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 4.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Since&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39; -&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;for the reason that; because.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;delegates were delighted, &lt;strong&gt;since &lt;/strong&gt;better protection of rhino reserves will help protect other rare species&amp;quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Once&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39; -&lt;/span&gt;on one occasion or for one time only.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&amp;quot;they deliver &lt;strong&gt;once &lt;/strong&gt;a week&amp;quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As much as​&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;-&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;used to say that two things are equal in amount or degree.&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;He likes hockey &lt;strong&gt;as much as&lt;/strong&gt; he likes basketball.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option 2.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the given sentence, we need to use the future perfect tense.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;future perfect tense&lt;/strong&gt; is used when action will have been completed at some point in the future.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The speaker&amp;#39;s parents will also reach in the future i.e. by next Monday.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Clearly, only option 2 is in the future perfect tense.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Correct sentence&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;-&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;My parents&amp;nbsp;will have reached&amp;nbsp;Delhi by Monday next.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
